The paper discusses using world knowledge for document clustering, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with information retrieval (IR) and computational linguistics (CL), which are covered by cs.IR and cs.CL respectively. Finally, the paper uses a knowledge base, which is related to databases (cs.DB).
